text: Kmele Foster (born October 31, 1980) is an American telecommunications entrepreneur and political commentator.NY Daily News article mentioning Kemele Foster as a telecommunications entrepreneur. http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/confidential/joe-not-so-true- blood-bachelor-article-1.1861091hpe.com article mentioning Foster as the co host of The Independents. http://www.hpe.com/opinion/x2058990051/Mike-Hughes- Obama-foreign-policy-chaos-now-disaster-later Foster is co-founder and Vice President of the telecommunications consultancy TelcoIQMSNBC interviewing Kmele Foster as the head of TelcoIQ. http://www.msnbc.com/afternoon-mojoe/how- entrepreneurs-can-get-ahead and is currently a co-host of the libertarian podcast The Fifth Column. ==References== ==Other websites== * Kmele Foster at Reason.com * Category:1980 births Category:Living people Category:American political writers Category:American political commentators Category:American television presenters Category:Writers from New York City Category:Television personalities from New York City
